# JFTL reference test corpus — chunk 9 (FINAL).
# Covers source lines ~2200-2635: remaining numeric-literal-precision tests,
# abs/fabs/length, keyword-as-variable/label-name tests, object construction
# edge cases, NaN parsing, input/debug, a long run of try/catch regression
# tests for issue #1859, explode/implode clamping, walk, float/NaN array
# slicing, setpath/ltrimstr/rtrimstr leak regressions, and finally the
# CVE deep-recursion stress tests at the very end of the file. Continues
# the ID sequence (435+) from chunk 8. This is the last chunk — after this,
# every line of the 2635-line source has been processed.
#
# Same caveats as prior chunks: not engine-verified.
#
# A recurring, genuine model gap shows up repeatedly in this chunk: JFTL's
# navigation grammar has no slice syntax (`.[a:b]`), so the entire float/NaN
# array-slicing section (tests around source lines 2435-2489) is skip, not
# because the arithmetic is hard but because there's no JFTL slice construct
# to express it in at all. Similarly, several tests here depend on jq's
# have_decnum arbitrary-precision-number flag, which has no JFTL analogue.

