13911860366432382
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyeval=float(_) - 10"}
}}}
COMMENT=Forcing float(_) replicates jq's double-precision truncation regardless of whether JFTL's own number model preserves big-int precision internally, since it forces the same IEEE-754 rounding jq applies once arithmetic touches the value. Not hand-verified bit-for-bit.

