}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
[true]
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyeval=sorted(set(abs(x) == abs(x) for x in _))"}
}}}
COMMENT=jq's length on a number equals its absolute value, so "abs == length" is really "abs(x) == abs(x)" here — tautological by construction, which is also why jq's own test always collapses to [true] regardless of the specific numbers.

