[504-run]
LEVEL=run
COMMENT=regression test for #3227
JQ = {{{
foreach .[] as $x (0, 1; . + $x)
}}}
INPUT = {{{
[1, 2]
}}}
EXPECTED = {{{
1
3
2
4
}}}
JFTL = {{{
{"main": "$pyrun=out = []\nfor init in (0, 1):\n    state = init\n    for x in _:\n        state = state + x\n        out.append(state)\nreturn out"}
}}}
COMMENT=jq's foreach init here is itself a two-value generator (0, 1), which reruns the ENTIRE foreach once per init value, concatenating both runs' outputs — replicated with an explicit outer loop over the two init values. Streaming gap: jq's 4 outputs collected into one array.

